===Etymology 1===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*per-|id=risk}}
From {{inh|en|enm|feer}}, {{m|enm|fere}}, {{m|enm|fer}}, from {{inh|en|ang|fǣr}}, {{m|ang|ġefǣr|t=calamity, sudden danger, peril, sudden attack, terrible sight}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*fērō}}, {{m|gem-pro|*fērą|t=danger}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*per-|t=to attempt, try, research, risk}}. Cognate with {{cog|nl|gevaar|t=danger, risk, peril}}, {{cog|de|Gefahr|t=danger, risk, hazard}}, {{cog|sv|fara|t=danger, risk, peril}}, {{cog|la|perīculum|t=danger, risk, trial}}, {{cog|sq|frikë|t=fear, danger}}, {{cog|ro|frică|frică}}. Doublet of [[peril]].

The verb is from {{inh|en|enm|feren}}, from {{inh|en|ang|fǣran|t=to frighten, raven}}, from the noun. Cognate with the archaic {{cog|nl|-}} verb {{m|nl|varen|t=to fear; to cause fear}}.

